1
00:00:01,180 --> 00:00:05,600
Support and resistance levels and supply and
demand zones are two trading concepts which

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,669
are closely related to one another.

3
00:00:07,669 --> 00:00:11,710
They each define points in the market where
the price is likely to reverse.

4
00:00:11,710 --> 00:00:15,900
The main difference between the two, is that
supply and demand areas have a zone which

5
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:20,820
you can use to look for entries, and support
and resistance levels are simply lines which

6
00:00:20,820 --> 00:00:22,210
you can monitor for entries.

7
00:00:22,210 --> 00:00:27,220
In today’s video I will share an effective
swing trading strategy and I will show you

8
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:34,440
how I combine both trading concepts to time
the markets and find high probability signals.

9
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:38,780
Many traders think there aren’t many differences
between supply and demand zones and support

10
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:43,170
and resistance levels, but in reality there
are actually quite significant, because having

11
00:00:43,170 --> 00:00:47,550
a zone you can use to watch for entries is
much easier than having a line.

12
00:00:47,550 --> 00:00:52,140
That, coupled with the fact that supply and
demand zones form less frequently than support

13
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:56,969
and resistance levels, means that it’s easier
to trade reversals from supply and demand

14
00:00:56,969 --> 00:00:59,640
zones than it is from support and resistance
levels.

15
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:03,390
And this is why the strategy of combining
both concepts work.

16
00:01:03,390 --> 00:01:08,100
The aim here is to combine the preciseness
of support and resistance levels with the

17
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:10,450
area aspect of supply and demand.

18
00:01:10,450 --> 00:01:16,350
In this way, we will be able to pinpoint entries
into supply and demand zones.

19
00:01:16,350 --> 00:01:20,610
The main problem with trading support and
resistance levels alone is the fact that the

20
00:01:20,610 --> 00:01:23,470
market will often fail to turn exactly on
the level itself.

21
00:01:23,470 --> 00:01:25,630
Tell me if this sound familiar.

22
00:01:25,630 --> 00:01:31,170
A lot of the time, price will either move
slightly beyond the level before reversing,

23
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:34,240
or will reverse before touching the level.

24
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:39,880
This can make trading support and resistance
levels quite a frustrating experience.

25
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:43,900
You almost never have this problem when trading
supply and demand zones.

26
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:48,150
The reason why is because the zones give you
an area in which you know the market should

27
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:49,150
reverse in.

28
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:54,030
You don’t really have to worry about a reversal
signal forming at an exact point, like you

29
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:58,450
do when trading support and resistance levels,
because you’ve got a whole zone you can

30
00:01:58,450 --> 00:02:00,400
use to watch for entries into trades.

31
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:05,030
You know that no matter where the reversal
signal ends up forming, as long as it’s

32
00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:09,709
found to be somewhere inside the supply or
demand zone, it’s a sign a reversal could

33
00:02:09,709 --> 00:02:12,180
be taking place.

34
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:16,739
Determining where support and resistance lines
are located is quite a simple process.

35
00:02:16,739 --> 00:02:20,560
For those of you who don’t know, support
and resistance lines are points where the

36
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:23,139
market has a high probability of reversing.

37
00:02:23,139 --> 00:02:27,250
The reason they have a high chance of causing
the market to reverse, is because the lines

38
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:31,230
are derived from the points where the market
has reversed in the past.

39
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:36,069
The idea is if the market has reversed multiple
times from roughly the same point in the past,

40
00:02:36,069 --> 00:02:39,719
then it has a good chance of doing the same
in the future.

41
00:02:39,719 --> 00:02:43,999
This means all we need to do to identify where
support and resistance lines are located in

42
00:02:43,999 --> 00:02:49,469
the market, is look for the points where multiple
reversals originated from similar prices to

43
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:50,609
one another.

44
00:02:50,609 --> 00:02:55,689
Here’s an example with multiple reversals
which took place.

45
00:02:55,689 --> 00:03:01,370
You can see that each of the reversals originated
from prices which are quite close to one another.

46
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:06,599
This tells us that a resistance line must
be found somewhere close to where these reversals

47
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:07,599
started.

48
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:10,059
And here are other multiple reversals.

49
00:03:10,059 --> 00:03:15,889
Again, each one of the reversals you see here
started from similar prices, which means there’s

50
00:03:15,889 --> 00:03:18,370
a support line around here.

51
00:03:18,370 --> 00:03:23,839
Now, because this is a swing trading approach,
meaning the lowest time frame I would analyze

52
00:03:23,839 --> 00:03:29,010
the market is the one hour chart, I look for
the big round numbers which are closest to

53
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:33,530
the lines I marked through the reversals which
took place at similar prices.

54
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:37,629
The reason why support and resistance lines
are always found to be at big round number

55
00:03:37,629 --> 00:03:42,370
levels is because of a phenomenon called order
clustering.

56
00:03:42,370 --> 00:03:48,229
Order clustering is where orders will accumulate
around round number levels in the market.

57
00:03:48,229 --> 00:03:53,359
So, in the first step of our strategy, you
have to identify the support and resistance

58
00:03:53,359 --> 00:03:57,609
lines by marking the points where multiple
reversals occurred on your chart.

59
00:03:57,609 --> 00:04:03,879
Then you have to mark the round numbers, which
are found closest to these reversals, and

60
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:10,499
finally, you have to move the lines so they
sit on top of the round number prices.

61
00:04:10,499 --> 00:04:14,930
Here you can see what the chart looks like
once I’ve adjusted the reversals lines to

62
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:16,669
go through the round numbers.

63
00:04:16,669 --> 00:04:20,909
These lines are now the correct support and
resistance lines you will use to look for

64
00:04:20,909 --> 00:04:26,909
entries into buy trades if the market returns
to the lines in the future.

65
00:04:26,909 --> 00:04:31,050
The second step consists in drawing supply
and demand zones.

66
00:04:31,050 --> 00:04:36,080
Supply zones can be located by looking for
a major drop away from either a single candle

67
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,610
or small consolidation structure.

68
00:04:38,610 --> 00:04:43,560
You mark the supply zone from the open of
last BULLISH candle before the drop and the

69
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:47,680
most recent high before the drop.

70
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:51,879
Demand zones are found when the market makes
a large move up from a single candle or a

71
00:04:51,879 --> 00:04:53,120
consolidation structure.

72
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:58,530
You mark the demand zone from the open of
last BEARISH candle before the drop and the

73
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:01,550
most recent low before the up move.

74
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:05,389
If you want more details about supply and
demand zones, make sure you watch this video

75
00:05:05,389 --> 00:05:07,469
first.

76
00:05:07,469 --> 00:05:10,620
Third step is to identify confluence areas.

77
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:14,759
If you combine support and resistance levels
with supply and demand zones you can get the

78
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:16,800
best of both worlds.

79
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:21,240
You can eliminate the issue not knowing if
the market failing to touch the level or just

80
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:26,580
moving beyond the level is still a reversal
signal, whilst also having a better idea of

81
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:30,870
where a reversal out of the supply or demand
zone is likely to take place from.

82
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:36,630
Here’s an example of a demand zone which
caused a reversal to take place.

83
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:41,439
The lines you see here are all the support
and resistance levels which had formed inside

84
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:43,210
the demand zone.

85
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:47,960
The market reversed out of the zone after
hitting the lower support level found at this

86
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,530
round number.

87
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:52,830
Here’s another demand zone.

88
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:57,520
This zone also contained three support levels
which had the potential to cause the market

89
00:05:57,520 --> 00:06:00,069
to reverse once it entered the zone.

90
00:06:00,069 --> 00:06:04,599
In real time, you wouldn’t know which of
these levels the market was going to reverse

91
00:06:04,599 --> 00:06:09,419
at before the price dropped into it, you would
just know that it’s almost certain for it

92
00:06:09,419 --> 00:06:12,100
to reverse at one of these levels.

93
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:17,449
In this instance it ended up turning once
it hit the support level found at this round

94
00:06:17,449 --> 00:06:18,990
number price.

95
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:24,310
If we go onto the 15 minute chart you can
see that when the market hit the support level

96
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:28,190
a couple of bullish engulfing candles began
to form.

97
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:32,389
You could have used these engulfing candles
to get a buy trade placed to take advantage

98
00:06:32,389 --> 00:06:37,330
of the reversal, knowing that any reversal
out of the demand zone is likely to begin

99
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:41,520
once the market has hit one of the support
levels inside the zone.

100
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:46,280
How To Trade Support And Resistance Levels
Inside Supply And Demand Zones

101
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:51,509
Like I said, the reality is that that you
don’t know which support or resistance level

102
00:06:51,509 --> 00:06:56,520
inside the zone is going to cause the market
to reverse, and this means that you can’t

103
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:59,270
really use a pending order to enter a trade.

104
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:04,409
The only other option is to watch for a price
action signal to form when the market hits

105
00:07:04,409 --> 00:07:06,830
one of the support or resistance levels.

106
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:11,919
Now, once you’ve got the support and resistance
levels and supply and demand zones marked

107
00:07:11,919 --> 00:07:15,999
correctly, you need to begin watching the
levels for potential entries.

108
00:07:15,999 --> 00:07:21,129
The best way of doing this is to switch to
a lower time-frame and monitor the price action

109
00:07:21,129 --> 00:07:27,270
that forms when the market starts to encounter
each of the levels inside the zone.

110
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:32,180
This example shows the price structure which
formed on the 15 minute chart when the market

111
00:07:32,180 --> 00:07:35,939
hit each support level found inside the demand
zone.

112
00:07:35,939 --> 00:07:40,719
You can see that when the market hit the first
support level a bullish engulfing candle formed

113
00:07:40,719 --> 00:07:44,060
and caused a slight move higher to take place.

114
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:48,320
This move ended up failing and caused the
market to fall down to the other support level

115
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,150
found below.

116
00:07:50,150 --> 00:07:54,889
The second support level caused another engulfing
candle to form and pushed the market above

117
00:07:54,889 --> 00:07:58,949
the high of the upswing created.

118
00:07:58,949 --> 00:08:03,199
There are two ways in which you could have
traded the bullish engulfing candles.

119
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:06,990
After seeing one of the engulfing candles
form, you could have entered a buy trade with

120
00:08:06,990 --> 00:08:10,060
your stop loss placed below the nearest support
level.

121
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:14,200
Or you could have entered a trade with a stop
loss placed at the edge of the demand zone

122
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,840
itself.

123
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:20,389
Usually having the stop placed at the edge
of the zone is the better option, because

124
00:08:20,389 --> 00:08:24,969
it will save you from any spikes which may
occur after getting your trade.

125
00:08:24,969 --> 00:08:26,979
Lets take a look at another example.

126
00:08:26,979 --> 00:08:29,050
Here’s another demand zone.

127
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:34,610
I’ve marked the support and resistance levels
found in and around this demand zone on the

128
00:08:34,610 --> 00:08:35,610
chart.

129
00:08:35,610 --> 00:08:40,000
Lets now go down to the 15 minute chart to
see if there was a price action signal we

130
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:45,110
could have used to get a buy trade placed
when the market was inside this demand zone.

131
00:08:45,110 --> 00:08:50,199
On the 15 minute chart we can see that when
the market hit the support level found in

132
00:08:50,199 --> 00:08:54,370
the middle of the demand zone two bullish
engulfing candles formed.

133
00:08:54,370 --> 00:08:58,529
The first caused the market to move out of
the zone, but did not cause it to reverse

134
00:08:58,529 --> 00:09:03,709
completely, while the second did cause the
market to reverse out of the zone.

135
00:09:03,709 --> 00:09:08,519
You can also look for other price action patterns
to get your signal, pin bars representing

136
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:10,910
other great price action signals.

137
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:14,709
Your entry into this trade would be on one
of the bullish engulfing candles that formed

138
00:09:14,709 --> 00:09:17,490
after the market hit the support level.

139
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:22,139
Your stop loss on either trade would be placed
at the support level which makes up the edge

140
00:09:22,139 --> 00:09:24,990
of the demand zone.

141
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:28,670
When you’ve got yourself into a profitable
trade, and the market has reversed out of

142
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:33,240
the supply or demand zone, the final step
to do is take some profits off the trade,

143
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:37,050
to make sure you don’t end up coming out
of the trade with nothing if the price action

144
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:41,060
changes and causes the market to move against
your position.

145
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:45,421
The best time to take profits is after you’ve
seen the market makes a new higher high, if

146
00:09:45,421 --> 00:09:50,190
you’ve got a buy trade placed into the market,
or after a new lower low has formed, if you’ve

147
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,310
got a sell trade placed.

148
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:57,029
You either move you stop loss higher or you
partially close half of your position.

149
00:09:57,029 --> 00:10:02,759
Of course, exiting the trade always comes
down to your personal preference.

150
